"# The Book of Jesse

*Motoi Scheme for programmers who already ship in other languages.*

---

This is not a first programming book. This is a translation manual and an honest case. You already know how to write software. You already have taste. You already have a favorite. This book puts Motoi Scheme next to what you already do — Python, JavaScript, Clojure, Lua, Java, Rust, Ruby, Go, Haskell, Common Lisp — and shows you the shape of the same problem in both places.

Where Motoi does something the same as your home language, we say so and move on. Where it does something different, we show you the shape, and try to earn the difference.

We do not insult the other languages. They are honest choices for their contexts. You picked yours for reasons. What you get from this book is another tool, with its own reasons.

The last six chapters are about what Motoi is *good* at — macros as composition, sound-and-motion on one timeline, Cortex-backed programs that remember what you did, SLAT as substrate, the frozen core, and a full mini-tutorial on writing chip-tune demo-scene pieces.

By the end you should either be writing Motoi, or you should have a clear-eyed answer for why you're not. Both are fine.

— The Motoi maintainers, 2026
")
